The author reflects on their childhood dream of serving the nation from within the White House and how that dream has become a reality as they intern with the Office of Cabinet Affairs. They describe the office's role in coordinating the efforts of the Executive Branch and advising departments on carrying out the President's mission. The author also highlights the collaborative efforts of the President and his Cabinet, such as announcing plans to decrease bureaucracy during Infrastructure Week. They emphasize the shared dream of making America great again, regardless of background, and the belief that anything is possible when working together as one people and nation. The author, Lucas B. Drill, is a rising junior in the Joint Program between Columbia University and the Jewish Theological Seminary.